I get her to live as a fugitive?

102
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:19,600
{\an5}I have to clear my name.

103
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:21,600
{\an5}Otherwise I might as well be in jail.

104
00:05:21,680 --> 00:05:24,400
{\an5}But how? Starting where?

105
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:26,720
Dent once told me

106
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:28,600
I.A. secretly records and archives

107
00:05:28,680 --> 00:05:30,240
all their incoming calls on tape.

108
00:05:31,360 --> 00:05:35,880
Which means the eyewitness
who called into I.A.?

109
00:05:35,960 --> 00:05:37,440
The one they assumed
that was Pinkney?

110
00:05:38,680 --> 00:05:40,480
There could be a tape
with his voice on it.

111
00:05:42,080 --> 00:05:43,560
That's a hell of a long shot,
brother.

112
00:05:43,640 --> 00:05:49,960
{\an5}And if, okay, just saying if,
a tape like that exists,

113
00:05:50,040 --> 00:05:51,960
{\an5}it's gonna be locked up tighter
than a duck's ass

114
00:05:52,040 --> 00:05:53,280
{\an5}in I.A. evidence.

115
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:58,440
{\an5}It's why it's lucky for you,
Uncle Harvey has connections.

116
00:05:59,640 --> 00:06:02,200
{\an5}Hey. Ginny.

117
00:06:04,280 --> 00:06:07,560
{\an5}How's my favorite I.A. sugar plum?

118
00:06:09,320 --> 00:06:11,160
Well, why do you think
I'm calling, baby?

119
00:06:12,680 --> 00:06:14,240
Heard you're getting married.

120
00:06:14,320 --> 00:06:16,480
- She changed her mind.
- Smart girl.

121
00:06:20,080 --> 00:06:21,680
{\an5}You're an animal, Bullock.

122
00:06:21,760 --> 00:06:23,960
- You know that?
- Ma'am, I do, I do.

123
00:06:25,880 --> 00:06:28,320
- Come on, Bullock.
- Yeah, baby.

124
00:06:28,400 --> 00:06:31,240
I'll be right there.
Slow down for me for a sec.

125
00:06:35,840 --> 00:06:38,320
Hey. An hour.
Slip them under the door.

126
00:06:38,400 --> 00:06:40,200
{\an5}Come on, Bullock.
Ain't got all night.

127
00:06:40,280 --> 00:06:41,320
{\an5}Don't say a word.

128
00:06:43,640 --> 00:06:44,840
{\an5}<i>Daddy's coming.</i>

129
00:07:38,080 --> 00:07:39,240
Give me that.

130
00:07:39,320 --> 00:07:41,520
Oh, what's up, sweetheart?
What are you doing?

131
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:44,960
- What are you doing?
- Now, do it. Do it!

132
00:07:45,040 --> 00:07:46,040
Somebody help!

133
00:07:46,120 --> 00:07:48,200
- Do it!
- Hey!

134
00:07:57,520 --> 00:07:59,920
Get out of here. Go!

135
00:08:02,880 --> 00:08:04,320
Ma'am, are you okay?

136
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:08,640
- You're welcome.
- Hands up.

137
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:09,920
Or I'll blow your head off.

138
00:08:12,840 --> 00:08:14,360
G.C.P.D. You're under.

139
00:08:15,840 --> 00:08:18,520
- You're Jim Gordon.
- Listen to me.

140
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:21,400
This is Barkley,
over at Fifth and Spring.

141
00:08:21,480 --> 00:08:22,960
I got Jim.

142
00:08:24,360 --> 00:08:26,360
- Don't kill me.
- I'm innocent, you hear me?

143
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:31,720
All units,
it's Jim freaking Gordon.

144
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:32,880
I need backup now.

145
00:08:48,440 --> 00:08:50,240
Father, I only knew you a short time.

146
00:08:52,800 --> 00:08:55,760
But you came to me when I was alone

147
00:08:55,840 --> 00:08:57,200
in this cold, dark world.

148
00:09:00,040 --> 00:09:01,440
You gave me a family.

149
00:09:05,360 --> 00:09:06,840
I will never forget you.

150
00:09:08,520 --> 00:09:09,680
As long as I...

151
00:09:13,800 --> 00:09:14,880
Oh, Father.

152
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:26,160
What a bore that was.

153
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:28,000
Yeah, but the house is ours now,
and we're rich.

154
00:09:28,080 --> 00:09:29,120
Quiet.

155
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:36,560
- He loved us all so much.
- Indeed.

156
00:09:36,640 --> 00:09:38,560
But, Oswald, Oswald,

157
00:09:38,640 --> 00:09:42,600
as painful as this is,
we need to talk practicalities.

158
00:09:42,680 --> 00:09:45,840
Can I call you a cab,
or will you take the bus?

159
00:09:45,920 --> 00:09:48,000
I don't understand.

160
00:09:48,080 --> 00:09:49,720
Well, you're not returning
to the house with us.

161
00:09:51,080 --> 00:09:54,000
- But where shall I go?
- Anywhere but there.

162
00:09:54,080 --> 00:09:56,440
Oswald, I'm so happy that you
and your father reconnected.

163
00:09:56,520 --> 00:09:59,560
But he left the house
and the estate to me.

164
00:09:59,640 --> 00:10:01,680
And I'm simply not comfortable

165
00:10:01,760 --> 00:10:04,200
sleeping under the same roof
as a notorious murderer.

166
00:10:04,280 --> 00:10:06,320
But I'm not like that anymore.

167
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:09,720
I couldn't hurt a fly,
even if I wanted to.

168
00:10:09,800 --> 00:10:12,680
Please, my father was all that I had.

169
00:10:12,760 --> 00:10:14,880
We shared the same blood.

170
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:18,360
And he wanted us to be together.
He told me.

171
00:10:18,440 --> 00:10:20,680
Let me stay. I'll do anything.

172
00:10:25,880 --> 00:10:27,280
You are his blood.

173
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:30,120
We do need help around the house.

174
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:31,280
- Mother.
- Mother.

175
00:10:31,360 --> 00:10:34,640
Why waste good money on servants
when we have Oswald?

176
00:10:34,720 --> 00:10:36,520
I'll do anything.

177
00:10:36,600 --> 00:10:38,160
Well, you could start by getting rid

178
00:10:38,240 --> 00:10:40,840
of those disgusting flowers.
I've always detested lilies.

179
00:10:40,920 --> 00:10:42,880
Yes. Of course.

180
00:10:45,640 --> 00:10:47,400
You're not really letting him stay?

181
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:49,960
He's Elijah's only natural son.

182
00:10:50,040 --> 00:10:52,960
If he found the right lawyer,
he could make things difficult.

183
00:10:53,040 --> 00:10:55,240
Especially, if people look
into how his father died.

184
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:57,960
- So, we just live with him then?
- Yeah, we keep him close.

185
00:10:58,040 --> 00:11:00,400
And after a suitable
amount of time goes by,

186
00:11:00,480 --> 00:11:03,880
poor Oswald, overcome with grief,
will take his own life.

187
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:06,680
Till then, we have a free servant.

188
00:11:06,760 --> 00:11:08,160
I could fire the maid.

189
00:11:13,240 --> 00:11:16,120
I murdered my...

190
00:11:17,320 --> 00:11:18,440
Parents.

191
00:11:19,480 --> 00:11:20,920
I cut their throats.

192
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:26,120
